03:55.670 --> 03:57.280
-SAY, NEWMIE,
YOU SEEN MITCH?

03:57.846 --> 03:59.543
-NO, HE WENT TO GO
PICK UP A WAVERUNNER.

03:59.674 --> 04:01.110
-HE SHOULD'VE BEEN BACK BY NOW.

04:01.241 --> 04:02.633
HE'S NOT AT HEADQUARTERS.

04:02.764 --> 04:03.895
-THOUGHT HE MIGHT BE HERE.
-NO.

04:04.026 --> 04:05.462
-WELL UH, HOBIE
CALLED LOOKING FOR HIM,

04:05.593 --> 04:08.683
SAID HE WON THAT A&W
BODYBOARD CHALLENGE.

04:08.813 --> 04:11.163
SAID HE'S BRINGING
HOME A YEAR'S SUPPLY
OF CREAM SODA.

04:11.294 --> 04:12.991
-MITCH'LL GO THROUGH
THAT IN A MONTH.

04:13.122 --> 04:14.123
[LAUGHING]

04:15.211 --> 04:16.473
-I WONDER WHERE HE COULD BE.

04:16.603 --> 04:18.127
-YOU KNOW MITCH.

04:18.257 --> 04:19.433
HE PROBABLY FOUND HIMSELF
SOME BEAUTIFUL WOMAN

04:19.563 --> 04:20.608
AND CAN'T DRAG HIMSELF AWAY.

04:20.738 --> 04:23.437
[LAUGHING]

04:24.916 --> 04:27.441
-DON'T GO ON
ANOTHER DIVE, PLEASE!

04:27.571 --> 04:29.225
COME ON, I WANT YOU
TO MEET MY SISTER.

04:29.356 --> 04:31.096
-I WILL, CAROLINE.
I'LL MEET HER TONIGHT AT DINNER.

04:32.620 --> 04:34.012
I WANNA MEET YOUR SISTER,

04:34.143 --> 04:35.797
I WANT TO MEET
YOUR WHOLE FAMILY.

04:35.927 --> 04:38.147
I LOVE YOU, BUT I NEED TO
GET ANOTHER CORE SAMPLE.

04:38.278 --> 04:39.670
-SO WHAT ABOUT JORDAN?

04:39.801 --> 04:41.150
COME ON, HE'S YOUR PARTNER.

04:41.281 --> 04:42.194
HOW COME YOU HAVE
TO DO ALL THE WORK,

04:42.325 --> 04:43.326
ALL THE TIME?

04:43.457 --> 04:44.458
-I'M AN ENVIRONMENT ENGINEER.

04:44.588 --> 04:45.937
HE'S A BUSINESSMAN.

04:46.068 --> 04:47.678
SO I DO THE DIVING;
HE DOES THE DEALS.

04:47.809 --> 04:48.679
BYE.

04:51.116 --> 04:52.074
HEY.

04:53.467 --> 04:54.555
I LOVE YOU.

04:56.078 --> 04:57.775
TELL YOUR SISTER I
CAN'T WAIT TO MEET HER.

04:58.472 --> 05:00.082
AND IF DRAKE'S TRENCH
ISN'T TOO POLLUTED,

05:00.212 --> 05:02.606
I'LL BRING BACK SOME GIANT
CLAMS FOR DINNER, OKAY?

05:02.737 --> 05:03.999
-OKAY.

05:04.129 --> 05:05.392
I'LL BRING DESSERT.

05:25.063 --> 05:27.283
-I DON'T BELIEVE IT! HI!

05:27.414 --> 05:29.024
C.J.! HI!

05:29.154 --> 05:30.373
-DOES STEPHANIE KNOW
YOU'RE HERE?

05:30.504 --> 05:31.940
-NO. I WANTED TO SURPRISE HER.

05:32.419 --> 05:34.769
C.J., I AM ENGAGED.

05:37.162 --> 05:38.425
-WELL THAT'S
GONNA SURPRISE HER!

05:38.555 --> 05:39.991
-I MET HIM ON A GLACIER.

05:40.122 --> 05:41.558
-WELL THAT DOESN'T SURPRISE ME.

05:42.167 --> 05:43.647
LET ME SEE,

05:43.778 --> 05:45.301
HE'S EITHER AN
ENVIRONMENTALIST OR AN ESKIMO.

05:45.432 --> 05:47.782
-WELL, HIS NAME'S
FRANK RANDALL, SO--

05:47.912 --> 05:48.870
-HE'S NOT AN ESKIMO.

05:49.523 --> 05:51.176
-HE'S ACTUALLY
PARTNERS IN A COMPANY

05:51.307 --> 05:52.830
THAT MONITORS
CORPORATE AMERICA'S

05:52.961 --> 05:55.442
ENVIRONMENTAL COMPLIANCE
WITH GOVERNMENT REGULATIONS.

05:55.572 --> 05:56.965
-A WATCHDOG FOR THE PLANET!

05:57.095 --> 05:57.922
I LIKE HIM ALREADY!

05:58.053 --> 05:59.359
-OH, I LIKE HIM, TOO.

05:59.489 --> 06:00.882
STEPHANIE'S GONNA LOVE HIM,

06:01.012 --> 06:02.536
BUT, UH, HE'S MINE.

06:03.145 --> 06:04.712
SO WHERE IS SHE?

06:04.842 --> 06:06.496
-OH UM, STEPHANIE, SHE
JUST TOOK A NEW WAVERUNNER

06:06.627 --> 06:07.932
FOR A TEST RUN.

06:08.063 --> 06:08.890
OH, NO. THERE SHE IS!

06:09.020 --> 06:10.065
-OH, OKAY!

06:10.195 --> 06:11.196
I'M GONNA GO SEE HER.

06:11.327 --> 06:12.459
-SEE YA!
-SEE YA, BYE!

06:12.589 --> 06:15.810
[POP SONG PLAYS]

06:27.952 --> 06:29.476
-♪ CARRYING MY DREAMS

06:29.606 --> 06:31.565
♪ DON'T CARE WHAT THEY THINK

06:31.695 --> 06:33.088
♪ OUT HERE

06:35.525 --> 06:37.048
♪ I CAN BE MYSELF

06:37.179 --> 06:39.268
♪ THERE'S NOBODY ELSE

06:39.399 --> 06:40.661
♪ OUT HERE

06:43.098 --> 06:46.884
♪ FREE TO BE ONLY ME

06:47.015 --> 06:48.886
♪ RIGHT HERE

06:50.758 --> 06:54.457
♪ CAPTURING THE MOTION

06:54.588 --> 06:56.459
♪ RIGHT NOW

07:49.860 --> 07:51.471
♪ THE SKIES ARE BLUE

07:51.601 --> 07:53.734
♪ I'M BREAKING THROUGH

07:53.864 --> 07:55.866
♪ OUT HERE

08:07.530 --> 08:08.488
[GRUNTING]

08:11.316 --> 08:13.144
[TENSE MUSIC]

08:37.038 --> 08:38.648
[SHOUTING]

08:43.653 --> 08:44.915
[PANTING]

09:13.553 --> 09:15.206
-I GOT YOU. I GOT YOU.

09:15.772 --> 09:16.730
SIT DOWN HERE.

09:17.818 --> 09:18.688
-OH GOD.

09:19.689 --> 09:22.562
-SIT DOWN.
TAKE A DEEP BREATH, OKAY?

09:25.477 --> 09:26.304
-OH!

09:26.435 --> 09:30.352
[PANTING]

09:32.223 --> 09:33.268
OH.

09:33.398 --> 09:34.835
OH STEPHANIE, I'M SORRY.

09:34.965 --> 09:37.315
I'M SO SORRY ABOUT
THE WAVERUNNER.

09:37.446 --> 09:38.447
-OH!

09:38.926 --> 09:41.015
NOT HALF AS SORRY AS
MITCH IS GONNA BE.

09:41.145 --> 09:41.885
HE JUST PICKED IT UP.

09:42.016 --> 09:43.887
-OH!

09:44.018 --> 09:45.367
HE'S GONNA HATE ME!
IS HE GONNA HATE ME?
-NO! NO NO.

09:45.497 --> 09:46.281
IT DOESN'T MATTER.

09:46.411 --> 09:48.022
IT DOESN'T MATTER, OKAY?

09:49.937 --> 09:50.807
CAROLINE,

09:52.069 --> 09:53.462
WHAT ARE YOU DOIN' HERE?

09:56.334 --> 09:57.553
-I'M GETTIN' MARRIED.

09:59.163 --> 10:00.338
[LAUGHING]

10:00.469 --> 10:01.557
-YOU'RE GETTING MARRIED?

10:01.688 --> 10:03.037
-YES! [LAUGHING]

10:03.690 --> 10:04.647
-OH!

10:05.300 --> 10:06.431
[LAUGHING]

10:06.562 --> 10:09.652
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

12:19.739 --> 12:21.741
-SO, DEBRA, WAS IT WORTH IT?

12:24.700 --> 12:25.527
THE RISKS YOU TOOK,

12:25.657 --> 12:26.746
WAS IT WORTH ALL THIS?

12:29.009 --> 12:30.488
-IT'S NOT OVER YET.

12:30.619 --> 12:31.576
-TELL ME SOMETHING.

12:32.142 --> 12:34.318
IS HE MORE IMPORTANT
THAN YOUR SON?

12:36.843 --> 12:38.366
-LEAVE MY SON OUT OF THIS.

12:38.496 --> 12:39.802
-SETH, THAT'S HIS NAME.

12:39.933 --> 12:41.282
YOUR LITTLE BOY'S
NAME IS SETH, RIGHT?

12:41.412 --> 12:42.936
-I SAID LEAVE MY
SON OUT OF THIS.

12:43.675 --> 12:46.766
-I WOULDN'T RISK
NOT SEEING MY SON AGAIN
FOR ANYONE.

12:46.896 --> 12:48.202
-WELL YOU'RE DOING
JUST THAT BY TALKING.

12:48.332 --> 12:49.681
SHUT UP.

12:49.812 --> 12:52.684
-BUT I WOULD RISK
MY LIFE IN ORDER--

12:52.815 --> 12:54.469
-I SAID, SHUT UP!

13:23.280 --> 13:24.194
-THANK YOU, DOCTOR.

13:24.325 --> 13:25.282
CAROLINE!

13:27.328 --> 13:29.373
-STEPHANIE!

13:30.635 --> 13:32.420
[CRYING]

13:35.466 --> 13:37.425
THE COAST GUARD SAID THAT
IF THEY HADN'T FOUND HIM

13:38.382 --> 13:39.731
WHEN THEY DID,

13:41.472 --> 13:42.604
FRANK COULD BE DEAD.

13:45.215 --> 13:46.477
-WHAT DID THE DOCTOR SAY?

13:48.349 --> 13:50.742
-HE'S GOT A REALLY, REALLY
BAD CASE OF THE BENDS.

13:52.309 --> 13:54.746
STEPHANIE, THEY DON'T KNOW IF
DECOMPRESSION CAN SAVE HIM.

13:56.400 --> 13:59.099
I LOVE HIM SO MUCH!

13:59.664 --> 14:01.449
[SOBBING]

14:02.276 --> 14:03.712
-HE'S GONNA PULL THROUGH.

14:03.843 --> 14:06.584
I KNOW IT. HE'S GONNA MAKE IT.
DON'T WORRY.

14:07.977 --> 14:10.066
-OH, I BEGGED HIM
NOT TO GO. I DID.

14:10.850 --> 14:11.763
-CAROLINE,

14:13.809 --> 14:14.897
WHAT WAS HE DOING OUT THERE

14:15.028 --> 14:15.811
DIVING BY HIMSELF?

14:15.942 --> 14:16.812
-I DON'T KNOW.

14:18.770 --> 14:20.076
STEPHANIE, HE WAS
ALWAYS SO CAREFUL.

14:20.207 --> 14:22.122
I MEAN, FRANK IS THE
BEST DIVER I KNOW.

14:22.252 --> 14:23.123
I DON'T...

14:23.950 --> 14:25.560
I DON'T KNOW HOW
THIS COULD OF HAPPENED.

14:27.344 --> 14:28.432
-WELL THE IMPORTANT THING IS,

14:28.563 --> 14:29.869
IS THAT HE GETS BETTER.

14:29.999 --> 14:30.870
THEN HE CAN TELL US.

14:31.000 --> 14:32.175
-OKAY?
-OKAY.

14:32.306 --> 14:34.264
NOW, LOOK, LET ME
GET YOU OUT OF HERE

14:34.395 --> 14:35.526
SO YOU CAN GET SOME--
-OH NO!

14:36.049 --> 14:38.442
I-- NO. I MEAN,
I CAN'T LEAVE HIM.

14:40.880 --> 14:42.751
I MEAN, I CAN'T LEAVE
HIM ALONE LIKE THIS.

14:45.841 --> 14:47.364
OKAY, COULD YOU UH--

14:48.844 --> 14:50.759
COULD YOU JUST GO
TO FRANK'S HOUSE?

14:51.368 --> 14:53.327
FRANK HAS A HOUSE
ON TOPANGA BEACH,

14:53.457 --> 14:54.545
AND JUST UH...

14:56.112 --> 14:57.374
YOU KNOW, GET ME SOME STUFF,

14:57.505 --> 15:00.029
MY NIGHTGOWN AND
THINGS FROM MY SUITCASE.

15:00.160 --> 15:01.639
BECAUSE THEY TOLD ME
THEY'D BRING ME A BED

15:01.770 --> 15:02.640
SO I COULD STAY.

15:04.251 --> 15:05.208
-OF COURSE.
-OKAY.

15:06.253 --> 15:07.036
-I LOVE YOU.

15:07.167 --> 15:07.994
-I LOVE YOU.

15:09.734 --> 15:11.171
-I LOVE YOU.

15:12.433 --> 15:13.260
[SNIFFLING]

15:13.390 --> 15:17.046
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

15:31.321 --> 15:34.672
[TENSE MUSIC]

17:47.631 --> 17:49.938
-LOOK, WHY DON'T YOU
JUST LET ME GO, HUH?

17:50.069 --> 17:51.418
LOOK, I'LL JUMP OVERBOARD.

17:51.548 --> 17:52.767
I'LL SWIM.

17:52.897 --> 17:55.074
MAYBE I'LL MAKE
IT, MAYBE I WON'T.

17:55.639 --> 17:57.250
BUT THAT TAKES ALL THE
PRESSURE OFF OF YOU.

17:57.380 --> 17:59.121
-THE ONLY PRESSURE ON ME

17:59.252 --> 18:00.557
IS YOU THINKING YOU CAN DO
ANYTHING ABOUT THIS SITUATION

18:00.688 --> 18:01.602
AND YOU CAN'T.

18:02.298 --> 18:03.952
SO JUST SHUT YOUR MOUTH.

18:04.605 --> 18:05.997
OR YOUR SON WILL BE
AN ORPHAN TONIGHT.

18:06.694 --> 18:07.999
[GROANING]

18:08.130 --> 18:09.305
HEY, BABE, TRY--
DON'T TRY MOVING,

18:09.436 --> 18:10.437
JUST STAY WHERE
YOU ARE, ALL RIGHT?

18:10.567 --> 18:11.438
[GROANING]

18:15.006 --> 18:15.964
HANG ON, BABY.

18:18.140 --> 18:19.489
DON'T!

18:19.620 --> 18:21.578
I'LL KILL YOU. I SWEAR IT.

18:21.709 --> 18:22.579
NOW BACK UP.

18:23.276 --> 18:24.146
BACK UP!

18:24.755 --> 18:25.626
NOW!

18:27.454 --> 18:29.238
DON'T THINK I WON'T
STILL KILL YOU.

18:29.934 --> 18:30.848
NOW SIT DOWN.

18:30.979 --> 18:32.241
SIT DOWN!

18:41.163 --> 18:43.992
-MAN: ALL RIGHT, LIEUTENANT,
WE'RE GONNA DUST FOR PRINTS
ON THE WINDSHIELD.

18:44.906 --> 18:45.776
-ALL RIGHT.

18:46.516 --> 18:48.039
-NOBODY I TALKED
TO SAW ANYTHING.

18:48.170 --> 18:49.389
-SAME HERE.

18:49.519 --> 18:51.130
-WELL, THE HARBOR MASTER
SAYS THE ONLY

18:51.260 --> 18:52.218
VESSEL THAT LEFT THIS
AREA IN THE LAST FEW HOURS

18:52.348 --> 18:54.133
WAS A TRAWLER NAMED RETRIEVER.

18:54.263 --> 18:55.482
I PUT IN A CALL TO
THE COAST GUARD,

18:55.612 --> 18:56.831
SEE IF THEIR
CHOPPER CAN SPOT IT.

18:56.961 --> 18:58.485
-IT'S GETTING LATE.

18:58.615 --> 19:00.313
-YEAH, WELL LET'S
EXPAND OUR SEARCH HERE.

19:03.664 --> 19:05.448
-LOOK, PLEASE THINK, CAROLINE.

19:06.232 --> 19:08.234
HE FOUND PAPERS
INSIDE A METAL TUBE

19:08.364 --> 19:10.279
THAT WAS HIDDEN IN A
PLANTER ON THE DECK.

19:10.410 --> 19:11.237
WHAT ARE THEY?

19:12.107 --> 19:13.282
-I DON'T KNOW.

19:13.413 --> 19:14.327
-WELL, WHAT WAS
FRANK WORKING ON?

19:14.457 --> 19:15.850
-STEPHANIE, I DON'T KNOW!

19:15.980 --> 19:18.157
-SOMEONE BROKE
INTO HIS APARTMENT!

19:18.287 --> 19:20.420
THAT SAME SOMEONE MIGHT'VE
TRIED TO KILL HIM.

19:21.856 --> 19:23.118
-FRANK HAS THE BENDS.

19:23.727 --> 19:24.641
HOW COULD SOMEBODY
TRY AND KILL HIM?

19:24.772 --> 19:26.426
-THEY COULD HAVE.

19:26.556 --> 19:28.341
IT'S JUST A MATTER OF
FORCING HIM TO THE SURFACE

19:28.471 --> 19:29.429
BEFORE HIS AIR BUBBLES.

19:30.038 --> 19:31.648
THE FASTER, THE DEADLIER.

19:32.954 --> 19:33.911
[SIGHING]

19:35.652 --> 19:36.871
LISTEN, CAROLINE.

19:38.351 --> 19:40.440
HOW LONG HAVE YOU AND
FRANK KNOWN EACH OTHER?

19:43.530 --> 19:44.792
-FIVE WEEKS.

19:46.315 --> 19:48.230
-AND YOU FEEL
READY TO MARRY HIM?

19:48.970 --> 19:50.537
YOU DON'T KNOW
ANYTHING ABOUT HIM!

19:50.667 --> 19:52.887
-I KNOW EVERYTHING
ABOUT THIS GUY.

19:54.454 --> 19:55.411
I KNOW THAT I LOVE HIM.

19:58.109 --> 20:00.547
AND I KNOW THAT FRANK
DOESN'T CARE ABOUT MONEY.

20:00.677 --> 20:02.679
STEPHANIE, HE CARES
ABOUT SAVING THIS PLANET.

20:03.637 --> 20:05.204
JUST ONE OF HIS REPORTS

20:05.334 --> 20:06.988
COULD SHUT DOWN BILLION
DOLLAR CORPORATE POLLUTERS.

20:08.294 --> 20:09.512
-ONE OF HIS REPORTS.

20:09.643 --> 20:10.687
-YES!

20:11.558 --> 20:12.646
-THOSE ARE PRETTY
VALUABLE REPORTS,

20:12.776 --> 20:13.647
DON'T YOU THINK?

20:18.913 --> 20:19.783
LOOK, CAROLINE.

20:20.871 --> 20:23.526
WHAT ENVIRONMENTAL HAZARD
WAS FRANK INVESTIGATING?

20:26.137 --> 20:27.835
-I DON'T KNOW.
HE DIDN'T TELL ME.

20:31.142 --> 20:32.535
I MEAN, WE DIDN'T
TALK ABOUT HIS WORK.

20:32.666 --> 20:35.059
ALL WE TALKED ABOUT WAS US.

20:36.670 --> 20:37.845
AND OUR FUTURE.

20:43.372 --> 20:44.765
HIS PARTNER,

20:44.895 --> 20:46.157
I-- I COULDN'T GET
IN TOUCH WITH HIM,

20:46.288 --> 20:47.768
BUT MAYBE YOU CAN. UM...

20:48.508 --> 20:50.379
HE'S STAYING AT THE
RITZ-CARLTON IN THE MARINA.

20:50.988 --> 20:51.989
HE'LL KNOW EVERYTHING.

20:52.599 --> 20:53.513
-WHAT'S HIS NAME?

20:53.643 --> 20:54.818
-JORDAN.

20:54.949 --> 20:56.167
JORDAN STEWART.

20:57.168 --> 20:58.169
-OKAY.

21:26.023 --> 21:28.461
-MR. STEWART SWIMS 100
LAPS EVERY AFTERNOON.

21:29.766 --> 21:30.811
-HOW LONG HAS HE BEEN IN?

21:30.941 --> 21:32.378
-UH, HE JUST STARTED.

21:32.508 --> 21:33.466
-THANK YOU.

21:41.648 --> 21:46.653
[TENSE MUSIC]

22:12.983 --> 22:13.941
[SIGHING]

22:15.899 --> 22:17.031
-YOU'RE ONE HELL OF A SWIMMER.

22:17.161 --> 22:19.207
-SO ARE YOU.

22:19.338 --> 22:20.643
-JORDAN STEWART.

22:21.252 --> 22:22.123
-I KNOW THAT.

22:23.342 --> 22:24.560
I CAME HERE TO SEE YOU.

22:24.691 --> 22:26.083
-HE MUST'VE BEEN
DIVING FOR PLEASURE

22:26.214 --> 22:28.172
OR DOING SOME
RESEARCH ON HIS OWN,

22:28.303 --> 22:30.610
BECAUSE WE'D FINISHED THE
PROJECT WE WERE WORKING ON.

22:31.088 --> 22:32.133
-WHAT PROJECT WAS THAT?

22:33.264 --> 22:34.701
-WE BUSTED A CHEMICAL COMPANY

22:34.831 --> 22:37.225
THAT WAS ACCUSED OF
DISPOSING TOXIC WASTE

22:37.356 --> 22:38.661
IN THE OCEAN A FEW YEARS AGO.

22:39.270 --> 22:40.271
WE WERE ABLE TO PROVE

22:40.402 --> 22:41.751
THAT THEY DID DUMP ILLEGALLY,

22:41.882 --> 22:43.449
SO THEY GOT A PRETTY STIFF FINE.

22:43.579 --> 22:45.189
-WELL FRANK TOLD CAROLINE
THAT HE WAS DIVING

22:45.320 --> 22:46.452
FOR CORE SAMPLES.

22:46.582 --> 22:48.149
-YEAH, WELL THAT'S FRANK.

22:48.279 --> 22:49.977
HE'S ALWAYS OUT THERE SEARCHING,

22:50.107 --> 22:51.631
TESTING ON HIS OWN.

22:53.415 --> 22:56.462
HE'S ON A PERSONAL CRUSADE
TO SAVE THE WORLD'S OCEANS.

22:57.158 --> 22:59.595
MUST BE ALL THAT TIME HE
SPENT WITH GREENPEACE.

23:01.249 --> 23:02.381
-HOW DID YOU TWO MEET?

23:03.338 --> 23:07.168
-[SIGHING] OUTSIDE THE
NUCLEAR POWER PLANT.

23:07.777 --> 23:09.257
I WAS TRYING TO
GET A COURT ORDER

23:09.388 --> 23:11.607
TO BLOCK A SHIPMENT OF
SPENT PLUTONIUM RODS,

23:12.129 --> 23:13.522
AND FRANK, ON THE OTHER HAND,

23:13.653 --> 23:16.873
HE CHAINED HIMSELF TO
THE RAILROAD TRACKS

23:17.004 --> 23:19.310
AND HE WAS ABLE TO
DELAY THINGS LONG ENOUGH

23:19.441 --> 23:20.964
FOR MY COURT ORDER
TO COME THROUGH

23:21.095 --> 23:22.792
AND STOP THAT SHIPMENT.

23:23.619 --> 23:26.013
AND I WAS ABLE TO
CONVINCE HIM RIGHT THEN

23:26.579 --> 23:28.711
THAT WITH HIS
ENVIRONMENTAL FERVOR

23:28.842 --> 23:30.147
AND MY LEGAL EXPERTISE,

23:31.627 --> 23:33.673
IF WE WORKED TOGETHER
WITHIN THE SYSTEM,

23:33.803 --> 23:35.109
WE COULD DO AN AWFUL LOT MORE

23:35.239 --> 23:36.676
TO HELP CLEAN UP
THIS PLANET OF OURS

23:36.806 --> 23:39.418
THAN EITHER ONE OF US
COULD INDIVIDUALLY.

23:40.244 --> 23:41.811
-JORDAN, WHAT DO YOU
THINK THE ODDS ARE

23:41.942 --> 23:43.552
OF FRANK GETTING THE
BENDS BY ACCIDENT?

23:44.379 --> 23:45.946
-[SIGHING] WELL,
THE GUY'S RECKLESS.

23:46.076 --> 23:47.556
HE TAKES CHANCES.

23:48.252 --> 23:50.080
CHAINED HIMSELF TO
THE RAILROAD TRACKS.

23:50.690 --> 23:53.040
I WAS ALWAYS HAVING TO
TELL HIM TO BE CAREFUL.

23:53.997 --> 23:56.565
HAS HE REGAINED
CONSCIOUSNESS AT ALL?

23:56.696 --> 23:58.480
BEEN ABLE TO SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED TO HIM?

23:58.611 --> 23:59.655
-NO.

24:00.308 --> 24:01.831
-WHERE IS HE? WHAT FACILITY?

24:01.962 --> 24:03.703
-PACIFICA INSTITUTE.

24:03.833 --> 24:05.139
THE MARINE RESEARCH CENTER.

24:05.269 --> 24:06.749
-I KNOW A SPECIALIST,

24:06.880 --> 24:08.969
A DOCTOR OF HYPERBARIC MEDICINE.

24:09.099 --> 24:10.318
I'LL GET HIM TO COME BY.

24:11.188 --> 24:12.407
-THANK YOU.

24:12.538 --> 24:14.453
-HEY, NO PROBLEM, AND LISTEN.

24:15.715 --> 24:16.716
FRANK'S TOUGH.

24:16.846 --> 24:17.717
HE'LL PULL THROUGH.

24:17.847 --> 24:18.674
DON'T YOU WORRY.

24:19.196 --> 24:20.459
OKAY?
-OKAY.

24:21.024 --> 24:22.461
NICE TO MEET YOU.

24:39.652 --> 24:40.740
-YOU'RE PROBABLY THINKING,

24:40.870 --> 24:42.219
HOW COULD THIS GUY KILL ME?

24:43.177 --> 24:44.918
I SAVED HIS LIFE.

24:48.269 --> 24:50.184
AH, BUT IT'S NOTHIN'
PERSONAL, THOUGH, WAS IT?

24:50.793 --> 24:51.751
-DOES IT MATTER?

24:53.230 --> 24:54.014
[CHUCKLING]

24:54.144 --> 24:55.145
-NOPE!

24:55.755 --> 24:57.104
-STOP TALKING. COME ON, EAT.

24:57.234 --> 24:58.105
EAT.

24:59.367 --> 25:01.369
-TELL THE CAPTAIN
TO GET UNDERWAY.

25:01.978 --> 25:03.850
TELL HIM TO HEAD TOWARD
THE MEXICAN BORDER.

25:04.503 --> 25:05.416
NOW!

25:30.398 --> 25:31.834
-WHAT DID DR. SHAPIRO SAY?

25:33.575 --> 25:35.098
-JUST THAT HE'S
IN MID-TREATMENT.

25:36.578 --> 25:38.014
I MEAN, HE IS RE-COMPRESSED.

25:39.363 --> 25:41.409
AND I GUESS ALL WE
CAN DO NOW IS WAIT.

25:43.846 --> 25:45.065
-WHY DON'T YOU GO
LAY DOWN AND REST?

25:45.195 --> 25:46.632
-NO.

25:46.762 --> 25:49.156
-LISTEN, I WILL CALL
YOU IF ANYTHING CHANGES.

25:50.244 --> 25:51.114
COME ON.

25:52.376 --> 25:53.856
I BROUGHT A BED IN FOR YOU.

25:54.422 --> 25:56.076
YOU'LL JUST BE IN THE NEXT ROOM.

25:57.730 --> 25:59.035
-I LOVE YOU.

25:59.949 --> 26:01.037
-I LOVE YOU, TOO.

26:03.170 --> 26:04.040
GO ON.

26:05.738 --> 26:06.565
-OKAY.

26:11.613 --> 26:12.875
[SIGHING]

26:13.615 --> 26:18.620
[TENSE MUSIC]

27:08.888 --> 27:10.454
-JORDAN, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

27:10.585 --> 27:11.586
-OH!

27:12.065 --> 27:14.807
HI, I DIDN'T KNOW YOU WERE HERE.

27:14.937 --> 27:16.460
-WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

27:16.591 --> 27:19.159
-OH, I'M SORRY, STEPHANIE,
THIS IS DR. HUNTINGTON,

27:19.289 --> 27:20.377
THE SPECIALIST I TOLD YOU ABOUT?

27:22.031 --> 27:24.251
HE'S PREPARING THE CHAMBER,
SO HE CAN OPEN IT

27:24.381 --> 27:25.208
AND EXAMINE FRANK.

27:25.339 --> 27:26.732
-NO.

27:26.862 --> 27:27.820
-HE'S RE-COMPRESSED.

27:27.950 --> 27:29.256
-IT DOESN'T MATTER.

27:30.039 --> 27:32.041
WHAT HAPPENED TO FRANK
MIGHT'VE BEEN AN ACCIDENT,

27:32.781 --> 27:34.261
BUT IT ALSO MIGHT'VE
BEEN DELIBERATE.

27:34.391 --> 27:35.871
UNTIL WE KNOW EXACTLY
WHAT HAPPENED,

27:36.002 --> 27:37.568
I DON'T THINK ANYBODY BUT
HIS PERSONAL PHYSICIAN

27:37.699 --> 27:38.569
SHOULD OPEN THE CHAMBER.

27:41.790 --> 27:44.445
-I APPRECIATE YOUR
CONCERN, REALLY I DO,

27:44.575 --> 27:47.491
BUT I'VE KNOWN FRANK AN AWFUL
LOT LONGER THAN YOU HAVE,

27:47.622 --> 27:49.189
AND I'M GONNA DO
EVERYTHING I KNOW HOW

27:49.319 --> 27:51.408
TO MAKE SURE HE GETS THE
BEST PHYSICIAN AVAILABLE.

27:51.539 --> 27:53.062
DOC.

27:53.193 --> 27:54.585
-YOU TOUCH THOSE CONTROLS,
AND I'LL CALL SECURITY.

27:55.195 --> 27:56.805
-STEPHANIE,

27:57.327 --> 27:58.938
YOU'RE ACTING LIKE
YOU DON'T TRUST ME.

27:59.547 --> 28:00.635
-WHY SHOULD I?

28:00.766 --> 28:01.810
I DON'T EVEN KNOW YOU.

28:02.811 --> 28:04.421
I DON'T EVEN KNOW IF WHAT
YOU TOLD ME THIS AFTERNOON

28:04.552 --> 28:05.727
WAS THE TRUTH OR A LIE.

28:07.468 --> 28:08.556
BUT WHAT I DO KNOW
IS THAT MY SISTER

28:08.687 --> 28:10.166
IS IN LOVE WITH THAT MAN,

28:10.297 --> 28:12.255
AND I'LL DO WHATEVER I
CAN TO PROTECT THEM BOTH.

28:20.089 --> 28:23.353
LOOK, IF AN APOLOGY IS
IN ORDER, I'LL APOLOGIZE

28:24.354 --> 28:25.399
TO BOTH OF YOU,

28:26.792 --> 28:28.445
BUT FOR NOW, YOU'RE
WELCOME TO STAY

28:28.576 --> 28:31.622
AND SEND YOUR POSITIVE
VIBES TO FRANK, OR LEAVE.

28:40.414 --> 28:41.589
-WHAT DO YOU THINK?

28:43.286 --> 28:44.505
-WITHOUT A PHYSICAL
EXAMINATION,

28:44.635 --> 28:45.854
IT'S DIFFICULT TO SAY.

28:47.551 --> 28:49.858
BUT IF HE DOESN'T REGAIN
CONSCIOUSNESS BY MORNING,

28:50.598 --> 28:51.904
IT'S DOUBTFUL HE EVER WILL.

28:56.082 --> 29:00.042
-WELL, WE'LL HAVE TO SEND
HIM OUR POSITIVE VIBES

29:00.173 --> 29:01.391
AND HOPE FOR THE BEST.

29:03.350 --> 29:05.439
OTHERWISE WE MAY NEVER KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO FRANK.

29:07.658 --> 29:08.529
DOC.

29:10.661 --> 29:12.098
GOODNIGHT, STEPHANIE.

29:28.767 --> 29:30.725
-ARE YOU SURE
THAT'S WHAT HE SAID?

29:31.508 --> 29:32.422
-DRAKE'S TRENCH.

29:33.554 --> 29:35.121
I REMEMBERED IT IN MY DREAM,

29:36.209 --> 29:37.950
BECAUSE HE SAID THAT IF
IT WASN'T TOO POLLUTED,

29:38.080 --> 29:40.779
HE WAS GONNA BRING ME
BACK SOME GIANT CLAMS.

29:43.042 --> 29:44.086
-CAROLINE, LISTEN.

29:44.739 --> 29:46.741
I NEED TO USE FRANK'S DIVE BOAT.

29:46.872 --> 29:48.308
-WHY?

29:49.004 --> 29:52.312
OH, NO. STEPHANIE,
PLEASE DON'T GO THERE!
-NO. I WILL BE FINE.

29:52.442 --> 29:53.792
I KNOW WHERE IT IS.

29:54.662 --> 29:57.970
JUST DON'T LET ANYBODY EXCEPT
FOR DR. SHAPIRO NEAR FRANK.

29:58.100 --> 30:00.102
ESPECIALLY NOT JORDAN STEWART.

30:00.624 --> 30:02.191
-JORDAN? WHY NOT JORDAN?

30:03.149 --> 30:04.454
-JUST DO WHAT I TELL YOU, OKAY?

30:05.238 --> 30:06.108
-OKAY.

30:33.657 --> 30:35.529
OH MY GOD!

30:39.576 --> 30:40.926
FRANK!

30:41.056 --> 30:43.363
OH, THANK GOD, FRANK!

30:50.196 --> 30:51.501
OH!

30:52.938 --> 30:55.897
-THE COAST GUARD CHOPPER
SPOTTED IT TEN MILES OFF OF
PORT SEGUNDO.

30:56.028 --> 30:58.160
ALL THE AGENCIES
ARE CONVERGING. GO!

31:17.527 --> 31:18.789
-HE'S BLEEDING AGAIN!

31:24.708 --> 31:25.492
-UNLOCK THESE.

31:25.622 --> 31:26.580
-NO!

31:27.363 --> 31:29.278
-YOU LET ME HELP YOU,
OR YOU'LL BLEED TO DEATH.

31:29.888 --> 31:30.801
-I DON'T TRUST YOU.

31:30.932 --> 31:32.107
I DON'T TRUST ANYBODY!

31:32.238 --> 31:33.021
-DEBRA: BRADY--

31:33.152 --> 31:34.109
-SHUT UP!

31:34.240 --> 31:35.806
HE'LL BLEED TO DEATH BEFORE ME.

31:35.937 --> 31:37.504
-AH!
-BRADY, NO!

31:37.634 --> 31:38.505
NO!

31:39.636 --> 31:41.334
-CAPTAIN: MISS HARRIS,
THERE'S BOATS COMIN'!

31:41.464 --> 31:42.683
POLICE AND LIFEGUARD.

31:42.813 --> 31:44.119
THEY'RE HEADING THIS WAY FAST!

31:49.037 --> 31:50.038
-GARNER: THERE IT IS!

31:55.174 --> 31:56.175
[GRUNTING]

32:13.366 --> 32:14.367
[GRUNTING]

32:18.806 --> 32:19.938
[GRUNTING]

33:01.544 --> 33:02.458
[SHOUTING]

33:03.982 --> 33:07.898
[UPBEAT MUSIC]

33:16.211 --> 33:17.212
-LOOK!

33:25.090 --> 33:26.917
[GRUNTING]

33:31.139 --> 33:32.314
[GROANING]

33:32.445 --> 33:33.663
-ALL RIGHT, HOLD IT!
DON'T MOVE!

33:56.338 --> 33:57.818
-MITCH, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

33:58.427 --> 33:59.820
-YEAH, I'M FINE!

33:59.950 --> 34:01.082
WE GOTTA GET HIM TO
A HOSPITAL, THOUGH!

34:01.213 --> 34:02.823
-HEADQUARTERS JUST
GOT A PANICKED CALL

34:02.953 --> 34:04.607
FROM STEPHANIE'S SISTER.

34:04.738 --> 34:05.913
SHE SAID SOMEONE TRIED
TO KILL HER BOYFRIEND

34:06.044 --> 34:07.393
IN DRAKE'S TRENCH YESTERDAY.

34:07.523 --> 34:08.829
STEPHANIE'S ON HER WAY THERE.

34:08.958 --> 34:10.351
-DRAKE'S TRENCH?

34:11.701 --> 34:12.920
THAT'S NOT FAR.

34:14.139 --> 34:15.444
TELL 'EM WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

35:21.467 --> 35:23.512
-MAN: UH, NO ONE'S HERE.
THEY MUST BE UNDERWATER.

35:23.643 --> 35:27.429
[OMINOUS MUSIC]

36:04.074 --> 36:05.946
-GARNER: THERE'S THE
BOAT STEPHANIE BORROWED.

36:17.305 --> 36:18.524
MITCH!

36:18.654 --> 36:19.699
-YEAH?

36:21.440 --> 36:23.355
-WHERE'S THIS GUY OFF
TO IN SUCH A HURRY?

36:23.485 --> 36:24.878
-JUMPERS OFF.

36:25.008 --> 36:26.401
CATCH HIM AND FIND OUT.

36:47.509 --> 36:48.902
-DON'T TAKE TOO LONG.

36:49.598 --> 36:54.603
[EXCITING MUSIC]

38:04.325 --> 38:05.979
-THIS IS THE L.A.
COUNTY LIFEGUARD.

38:06.109 --> 38:08.111
TURN OFF YOUR
ENGINES IMMEDIATELY!

38:10.766 --> 38:12.942
I REPEAT, TURN OFF YOUR ENGINES!

38:13.073 --> 38:14.074
-LET ME HANDLE THIS.

38:17.164 --> 38:19.514
-UNLESS YOU WANT TO
COME TO A DEAD STOP,

38:19.645 --> 38:21.690
TURN OFF YOUR ENGINES NOW!

38:46.454 --> 38:47.542
-I'LL BE RIGHT BACK, MITCH!

38:47.673 --> 38:49.022
-WHAT NOW?

38:49.152 --> 38:51.198
-I'VE GOTTA GO GET
WHAT I CAME HERE FOR.

38:51.720 --> 38:56.029
[EXCITING MUSIC]

39:16.223 --> 39:18.530
-I'M REALLY HAPPY
THAT FRANK'S ALL RIGHT.

39:19.139 --> 39:22.490
-HE STILL CAN NOT BELIEVE THAT
JORDAN TRIED TO KILL HIM,

39:22.621 --> 39:24.797
OR THAT YOU WENT DOWN
FOR ANOTHER CORE SAMPLE.

39:24.927 --> 39:26.799
-NOW JORDAN WON'T BE
ABLE TO SWITCH THEM

39:26.929 --> 39:28.366
AND FALSIFY THE REPORT.

39:28.496 --> 39:30.237
-I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHY THE CHEMICAL COMPANY

39:30.368 --> 39:31.804
WOULD TRY AND BRIBE JORDAN,

39:31.934 --> 39:33.501
IF THEY STILL HAD TO
PAY THE FINES ANYWAY.

39:33.632 --> 39:35.938
-WELL, THOSE FINES WERE
FOR DUMPING ILLEGALLY.

39:36.069 --> 39:38.332
AND THE FALSIFIED REPORT
SAID IT WASN'T TOXIC,

39:38.463 --> 39:39.986
SO THE FINES WERE A LOT LESS,

39:40.116 --> 39:41.509
AND AN ENVIRONMENTAL CLEANUP

39:41.640 --> 39:43.946
THAT WAS REALLY EXPENSIVE
WASN'T REQUIRED.

39:44.860 --> 39:46.906
BUT NOW THEY'RE GONNA HAVE
TO PAY FOR IT WITH PRISON.

39:47.036 --> 39:48.473
-SEE?

39:48.603 --> 39:49.952
WOULDN'T YOUR LIFE
BE BORING WITHOUT ME?

39:50.562 --> 39:51.345
-NO.

39:51.476 --> 39:52.781
[LAUGHING]

39:52.912 --> 39:54.217
-NO?

39:59.179 --> 40:00.049
-DAD!

40:00.659 --> 40:01.399
DAD!

40:01.529 --> 40:02.443
-MITCH: HOBESTER!

40:02.574 --> 40:04.053
-I WON!

40:04.184 --> 40:06.099
-YOU'RE KIDDING!
-I WON THE A&W, THE TROPHY.

40:06.229 --> 40:07.579
EVERYTHING WAS AWESOME!

40:07.709 --> 40:08.493
-ALL RIGHT!

40:08.623 --> 40:09.972
FANTASTIC, MAN!

40:10.103 --> 40:10.973
-SO UH,

40:11.583 --> 40:13.019
WHAT'D YOU DO THIS WEEKEND?

40:13.149 --> 40:14.455
DO ANYTHING EXCITING?

40:25.161 --> 40:26.685
-NAH.

40:26.815 --> 40:29.470
JUST ANOTHER TYPICAL
WEEKEND HERE AT BAYWATCH.

40:31.124 --> 40:32.212
-HOBIE COOL!

40:34.127 --> 40:36.782
[END THEME PLAYING]
